ach this!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering JVM instrumentation**\\n\\nI’m thinking about JVM with an agent and how it maps call sites from loaded classes when the bytecode is identical. But wait, what happens if the classes are loaded from a source context and not from the classpath with reload4j jar? I wonder how instrumentation sees that situation. It seems that the native approach won’t allow for building dynamic classes. Looks like I have a few things to clarify for better understanding!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Clarifying class dynamics**\\n\\nI’m considering importing PropertiesPatternConverter, and I wonder if it’s a dynamic class since it doesn’t seem to have dynamic call sites—just calls. It looks like it doesn’t lead directly to an active class. I’m thinking about one-to-one mapping: if I’m targeting MDCKeySetExtractor, I should ensure that any tests cover it directly or indirectly. Should I just use both options? That seems like a good plan!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Inspecting MDC properties**\\n\\nI'm thinking about the `event.getMDC(item.toString())` call and whether it properly checks `mdcCopy` first. I wonder if there could be an issue with the assert order in this context. It feels important to dig into this a bit further to clarify what happens in the mapping of properties. I'll need to take a closer look at the implementation to ensure everything is functioning correctly.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_q72nYLTNR8LBJwAIU0J1yEpw|fc_0643568f61f4f3c9016a110c1c4dc08191a6aa92e0aeef5fc7", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "rg \"Object getMDC\" -n ../../source_context/ch.qos.reload4j/reload4j/1.2.19/main/extracted/org/apache/log4j/spi/LoggingEvent.java && rg \"getMDC\" ../../source_context/ch.qos.reload4j/reload4j/1.2.19/main/extracted/org/apache/log4j/spi/LoggingEvent.java -n | head -20"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 743, "