e challenge is that the method signature at runtime will reference the old LoggingEvent. I might have to create an event with MDC and invoke a public method through reflection due to isolated classloading. But, it seems like direct public API access is difficult here. We might need to add tests to catch unsupported dynamic loading and discuss the concerns around it.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring serialization and method issues**\\n\\nI'm wondering if I could use serialization to construct the `getKeySetMethod`, which is marked as final and private. I’m concerned there might be system properties or security manager settings causing `LoggingEvent.class.getMethod` to fail during the constructor. With Java 21 removing the Security Manager, that complicates things. Also, I'm finding it strange that `getMethod` with null for parameter types behaves differently. In Java, `getMethod` uses varargs — does that change the expected outcome?\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering Gradle dependencies**\\n\\nI’m working through the idea that log4j might already be in the Gradle cache, but it’s not set as a dependency. I’m thinking about adding it as a testImplementation. However, I’m worried about potential conflicts from duplicate packages during test compile/runtime. If I create a separate configuration for it, it might not show up in the runtime classpath. I need to find a way to include the jar during testing, possibly with a new configuration.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_hWu3kYfaYSJ3XUvMfwYVobkE|fc_0643568f61f4f3c9016a110c83be4c8191a8d6c63eb205b197", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "grep -n \"class LogEvent\" -n ../../source_context/ch.qos.reload4j/reload4j/1.2.19/main/extracted/org/apache/log4j/pattern/LogEvent.java && grep -n \"class LoggingEvent\" ../../source_context/ch.qos.reload4j/reload4j/1.2.19/main/extracted/org/apache/log4j/spi/LoggingEvent.java"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "